info, I'm going to go back one slide really fast. So coefficient info is this list of

00:14:33.799 --> 00:14:39.559
tables. If I unnest on coefficient info, now I have this flat data frame that I can work

00:14:39.559 --> 00:14:44.059
with where I have for each one of my bootstrap data sets I have all the information that I

00:14:44.059 --> 00:14:49.520
need about my coefficients. So now if I want to plot this to visualize uncertainty, this is

00:14:49.520 --> 00:14:55.640
just a one liner or two liner in GG plot. Okay, five liner. But then you throw it in GG plot

00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:59.340
too and you just can see this right away. So I haven't done a whole bunch of bootstraps

00:14:59.340 --> 00:15:05.340
here but hopefully the idea is that the workflow is very convenient. Okay, there's kind of one

00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:11.919
last use case that you can use here. So suppose we want to do the same thing but we would like

00:15:11.919 --> 00:15:16.039
to visualize the uncertainty in our predictions. In that case what we're going to want to do

00:15:16.039 --> 00:15:20.760
is work with the augmented data sets. So we're going to apply the same strategy. We already

00:15:20.760 --> 00:15:26.460
have a table of fit models. We're going to map augment over those fit models and what we're

00:15:26.460 --> 00:15:31.080
going to get again is going to be this nested table with a bunch of predictions and then we

00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:37.460
can un-nest those nested predictions and GG plot them right away. And that looks like

00:15:37.460 --> 00:15:43.760
this. So now you have a bunch of non-linear fits that you're visualizing all at once. Okay,

00:15:43.760 --> 00:15:48.539
so that's what I use Broom most for personally. There's a bunch of documentation on how to

00:15:48.539 --> 00:15:55.039
use Broom. We just released Broom 0.50 at kind of the end of the summer. So there's a bunch

